President Cyril Ramaphosa is visiting a number of sites identified as COVID-19 facilities in Gauteng.Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa has thanked frontline health workers for their commitment, as the lockdown continues. At least 44 government workers have tested positive for Coronavirus in Gauteng. READ:Â Ramaphosa visits COVID-19 quarantine facility "Our frontline health workers are the real foot soldiers that we have to fight against this invincible enemy and we thank them, the country can't thank them enough and I will continue to thank them and recognise them for the excellent work that they are doing", said Ramaphosa. Gauteng currently has 1,252 confirmed cases and eight deaths. Ramaphosa, together with the provincial government visited several sites identified as COVID-19 quarantine facilities in the province. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.